<p>Gorgeous. Almost gorgeous enough to make me forget about my map.</p>
<p>Here we see that, with the data in the dataframe, the U.S. far surpasses its runner-up, the defunct USSR as well as its progeny, the Russian Federation. It has about 3 times as many golds as the next most successful <em>active</em> olympic competitor, Germany. In times of global and domestic turmoil, I suppose it is nice to find these little reasons to be patriotic.</p>
<p>I think I also want to make a line map showing the number of each medal type the U.S. has earned over the years. This will give us an idea of the breakdown of our athletes’ successes across the years.</p>
